Description: Body sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery vessel, possibly a krater; interior: reserved; exterior: dark grey slip; decoration in relief consisting of a tendril.
Curator's comments: Sherd joins British Museum 1888,0601.644.a. The fabric and decorative techinques find parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.644.c, which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen, Bonn (sample NAUK 47) and remained a chemical singleton.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.121)
